<F P=101> Uganda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Helicopter Crashes Near Gulu; 7 Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0702184594 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1700 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0702184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A military helicopter has crashed near Gulu town 
killing seven people. (?All those) on board including the pilot, 
Major William Andama, died in the crash. Three children in a 
house died instantly when the helicopter crashed into the house 
a few minutes after take-off. Entebbe Airbase Commander 
Lieutenant Colonel Joshua Natara said the helicopter which was 
on normal operation caught fire in mid-air and crashed into the 
house as it tried to land. The helicopter was coming to 
Kampala. The cause of the fire is not yet known, and experts 
have been despatched to the scene to carry out an investigation. 

</TEXT>

