<H3> <TI>   Vice President Meets OPEC Development Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0502162994 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 0700 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0502162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The visiting director general of the OPEC Fund 
for International Development, Dr. Sayyid 'Abdallahi, has been 
received by the vice president, Dr. Samson Kisekka. The meeting 
took place at the vice president's office in Kampala yesterday. 
  Dr. Kisekka expressed gratitude for the assistance which the 
OPEC Fund for International Development has given to Uganda to 
date. He briefed him about developments in Uganda today and the 
intention of the government to restore the country to normalcy. 
He informed him that the government is now trying to renew as 
much as possible all acquaintances after the political turmoil 
of the past. 
  Dr. 'Abdallahi expressed satisfaction with the cooperation 
his organization enjoys with Uganda. He said his delegation is 
in Uganda to make an on-the-spot inspection of their various 
projects in the country. He said that there are other areas 
which have been identified for cooperation and looked forward to 
the further strengthening of relations. [passage omitted] 

