Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Jonas Savimbi [leader of National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola - UNITA] has explained his absence 
from Houphouet-Boigny's funeral in Cote d'Ivoire by referring to 
the situation in Cuito. Despite that, Portuguese Secretary of 
State for Cooperation Briosa e Gala will take the opportunity to 
make some contacts concerning the war in Angola. More details 
from Cote d'Ivoire from Fatima Torres: 
  [Torres] [passage omitted] All the journalists have been 
talking about Angola, but with the absence of Portuguese 
President Mario Soares and UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi, the 
expectation of some impressions being exchanged on the Angolan 
issue have vanished. Eugenio Manuvakola confirmed that Savimbi 
is being represented here by his sister and the UNITA secretary 
general, due to the escalation of the fighting in Angola. 
  Everybody was expecting Jonas Savimbi to come here because 
he 
had a strong friendship and polical links with the deceased 
President Houphouet-Boigny. 
  On the other hand, the Angolan Government sent a strong 
representation headed by the parliament speaker and the foreign 
minister. [passage omitted] 

