<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Liberia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Reported Between NPFL, Peace Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0802101994 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0802101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thousands of people have been trooping into 
Buchanan, Grand Bassa County, over the last couple of days to 
escape the fighting between the NPFL [National Patriotic Front 
of Liberia] and an armed group calling itself the Liberian Peace 
Council. Our reporter, Hassan Kia, who just returned from 
Buchanan, said he saw hundreds of returnees and escapees 
including women with their malnourished babies on their backs. 
Our reporter said most of those who spoke to him looked weary 
and hungry because of the many days of walking in the bushes to 
get to Buchanan from [name indistinct] and its surrounding 
villages. They told our reporter that for nights, they came 
under heavy firing from the two warring sides. 
  Meanwhile, the Catholic Relief Service [CRS] has begun 
distributing emergency food ration to both the returnees and the 
escapees that are arriving in Buchanan and nearby towns. The 
employee of CRS catering for the influx said since yesterday, 
100 bags of rice, vegetable oil, and beans have been 
distributed. Each family, he said, received 20 cups of rice for 
new arrival ration, while efforts were being made to absorb them 
into other areas for regular relief supplies. 

</TEXT>

