<H3> <TI>   PDP Decides To Withdraw From Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0802091994 Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0802091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Party for Democracy and Progress [PDP] decided 
to withdraw from government yesterday afternoon. Among other 
things, the party disapproves of the Alliance for Democracy in 
Mali's attitude regarding the underlying principles of the 
Republican pact, as well as the management of public affairs. 
The party's decision follows the cabinet reshuffle, which 
confirmed the withdrawal of the National Committee for 
Democratic Initiative and the Rally for Democracy and Progress 
from the government. The PDP representative within the cabinet 
was Boubakar Karamoko Coulibaly at the Ministry of Youth and 
Sports. 

</TEXT>

