<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Namibia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Angolan MPLA Official Visits SWAPO Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0702195794 Windhoek Namibian Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 1900 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0702195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Windhoek Namibian Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Secretary General of the ruling MPLA [Popular 
Movement for the Liberation of Angola] party in Angola, Lopo do 
Nascimento, is in Namibia to discuss business-related issues 
with his SWAPO [South-West African People's Organization] 
counterpart Moses Garoeb. Garoeb told NBC [Namibian 
Broadcasting Corporation] news that the visit is a strictly 
party-to-party business mission, although political issues will 
also be discussed. He said both the MPLA and SWAPO have 
business interests which are supposed to help them become 
independent and self-reliant within the multiparty political 
environment. Garoeb revealed that some of the business 
interests to be discussed between the two parties will include 
fisheries and transportation. 

</TEXT>

