<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zimbabwe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister, Coetsee Establish Working Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802080094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] South Africa and Zimbabwe have laid the foundations 
for the first major cooperation agreement between the two 
countries in 14 years. The minister of justice and of defense, 
Mr. Kobie Coetsee, and his Zimbabwean counterparts, Mr. Emmerson 
Mnangagwa and Mr. Dumiso Dabengwa [name as heard], said after 
talks in Harare that a working committee had been established to 
oversee an exchange of information on matters such as the 
administration of justice, the combating of organized crime, and 
the resumption of an extradition treaty. The imprisonment in 
Zimbabwe of three South Africa agents had also been discussed, 
but Mr. Mnangagwa merely said that the men would be freed at an 
appropriate time. The men were sentenced to life imprisonment 
for bombing an ANC [African National Congress] house in 1988. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

