<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Blames Capital Flight on ANC Policies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802090494 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Home Affairs Minister Danie Schutte says nearly a 
million rands in capital is now leaving the country each month 
because of conflicting statements made by the ANC [African 
National Congress] on nationalization. Mr. Schutte told a group 
of Durban businessmen the role of the ANC, as the dominating 
partner in a future government, could also lead to foreign 
investor skepticism. The minister added that, last year alone, 
at least 9 billion rand had left the country. 

</TEXT>

