<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fierce Clashes Continue in Cuito; 175 Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0702194994 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1900 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0702194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Cuito by correspondent Abel Abraao] </F>
  [Text] Clashes continue in the city of Cuito between 
government and National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA] forces. Today, more than 5,000 shells were fired 
by UNITA at the martyred city of Cuito. The death toll 
resulting from UNITA's shelling has risen to 175. Hospital 
sources say about 350 people -- mostly children, elderly men, 
and women -- have been wounded. The hospital lacks the means to 
cope with the situation. 
  Today's clashes were fiercer than yesterday's. The city of 
Cuito has become a true inferno. Jonas Savimbi's UNITA 
continues to shell the city and mount strong attacks on it. The 
situation, however, is under the control of government forces, 
who continue to deal severe blows to the enemy of the people. 

</TEXT>

