<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italian Minister's Statements Called Misleading </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0902115094 Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic in 
Somali 1700 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0902115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A statement from the presidency says the Somali 
people are outraged by the disinformation from Italian Defense 
Minister Fabio Fabbri about the current situation in Somalia. 
The statement said the defense minister's utterances are far 
from the actual situation in Somalia. This is not the first 
time the Italian defense minister has issued such 
disinformation. The statement said it is unfortunate that such 
remarks should be made by an Italian senior minister, adding 
that it is an issue that could seriously dent the excellent 
bilateral relations and cooperation existing between the two 
nations. 
  The statement said it has become a habit of senior Italian 
officials to make misleading statements about Somalia with the 
deliberate intention of painting a negative picture of the 
prevailing situation in Somalia. The statement said the remarks 
made by the Italian defense minister are unfortunate, 
misleading, and made without proper research on the subject. 
  The statement said the recent confrontation that took place 
in Balcad, Shabeelaha Dhexe region, was caused by an intentional 
provocation by the Italian soldiers, which led to deaths and 
injuries on both sides. The statement said the Government of 
Somalia is optimistic that, in the future, Italian leaders will 
consult their representative in Somalia before uttering 
misleading statements that could cause disinformation about a 
particular incident. It warned Italian officers against 
dramatizing minor incidents as well as avoiding matters that 
might trigger provocation between Italian soldiers and the local 
people. The statement advised Italian soldiers and officers to 
carry out their duties in accordance with the UN Operation in 
Somalia mandate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

