<H3> <TI>   NRC Fails To Form Quorum, Adjourns `Indefinitely' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0802213694 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1900 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0802213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Resistance Council [NRC] has adjourned 
indefinitely after failing to form a quorum. At 2:30 P.M. this 
afternoon, the vice chairman of the NRC, Alhaji Moses Kigongo, 
called for an adjournment of 15 minutes to allow for more NRC 
members to come and form a quorum, as there were only 50 
members. After 25 minutes of waiting, the house was called to 
order, only to find that there was still no quorum. The house 
was set to deliberate on the government white paper on education 
and the public accounts committee report. 

</TEXT>

