<H3> <TI>   Shelling Continues 8 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802203094 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1900 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Cuito by correspondent Abel Abraao] </F>
  [Text] Several people died in the past eight hours in 
nonstop shelling by National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola bandits against the martyred city of Cuito. While the 
war claims more victims, famine increases every tenth of a 
second because relief operations have been suspended, affecting 
more than 130,000 people. Should the situation continue, famine 
and war could claim 50 lives daily. The hospital recently 
renovated by the Belgian organization Medecins Sans Frontieres 
has been shut down and the patients left to their own devices. 
Hospital sources say the hospital is providing only first aid 
treatment. 

</TEXT>

