<H3> <TI>   Renamo Gives Domingos, de Castro New Duties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0902061394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0400 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0902061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Raul Domingos, head of the Mozambique National 
Resistance, Renamo, Political Affairs Department and Renamo's 
second man, has been replaced and will now be involved full time 
in the Supervision and Control Commission, CSC. 
  In turn, Jose de Castro has been removed from his post as 
head of the Renamo Foreign Affairs Department. He is now in the 
National Elections Commission. 
  Jeronimo Malagueta and (Fight) have been appointed to 
replace 
those Renamo officials on an interim basis. A Renamo source has 
explained that those changes within the party aim at increasing 
Renamo's ability to deal with important issues pertaining to the 
country's peace process. 

</TEXT>

