<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Namibia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Holds Talks With RSA's Coetsee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0902094894 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0902094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Justice and Defense Minister Kobie Coetsee met his 
Namibian counterpart in Walvis Bay yesterday in an effort to 
promote cooperation in the administration of justice between the 
two countries. 
  This follows a meeting between the ministers of justice of 
South Africa and Zimbabwe on Monday [7 February], where a 
similar agreement was reached. Mr. Coetsee and Mr. Peter 
Mueshihange, the Namibian minister of defense, agreed on the 
phasing in of a Namibian military presence in Walvis Bay which 
will fall under Namibian rule in less than three weeks. They 
also discussed the final withdrawal of the SADF [South African 
Defense Force] from the enclave. Walvis Bay and the Guano 
Islands off the Namibian coast will be transferred to Namibia at 
midnight on February the 28th. 

</TEXT>

