<H3> <TI>   PDP Minister Coulibaly Decides To Remain in Cabinet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0902105394 Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0902105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We now know the final decision of Youth and Sports 
Minister Boubacar Karamoko Coulibaly in the wake of his talks 
with the head of state yesterday. While respecting the decision 
of his party, the Party for Democracy and Progress, to withdraw 
from the government, he says that, as a patriot, he is duty 
bound to pursue the work that he has started with the support of 
the Malian youth and sports community, in particular, and the 
Malian people, in general. As a result, Boubacar Karamoko 
Coulibaly says that, out of respect for the Malian people and as 
a citizen, he has decided to remain in the government in order 
to make his modest contribution to the construction of a 
democratic and prosperous Malian state. 

</TEXT>

