<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alliance: No More Concessions to Government, ANC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802204794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 2000 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Freedom Alliance says it will make no more 
concessions in talks with the government and the ANC [African 
National Congress]. At a leaders' summit that ended in Pretoria 
a short while ago, the alliance said any further initiative to 
break the deadlock in negotiations would have to come from the 
ANC. [passage omitted] We have a report from Gary Alfonso in 
Pretoria: 
  Freedom Alliance negotiators arrived for the summit to 
report 
back to their leaders about last night's deadlock. After a 
two-hour meeting, the writing was on the wall. Alliance 
Chairman Rowan Cronje said that their group could not and would 
not make any more concessions. IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] 
leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi said his party would not feel 
threatened by the looming deadline for parties to register for 
the election. That means if no compromise is reached on the 
issue of entrenching powers for regions in the constitution, the 
Alliance parties will not register, and that means that they 
will not take part in the election. The Alliance members say 
the ball, and their continued participation, is now in the hands 
of the ANC and the government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

