<H3> <TI>   Meyer: Alliance Withdrawal Minimizes Political Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0902074394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0902074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Freedom Alliance says its leaders are unable 
to make further concessions to reopen the constitutional 
negotiations with the government and the ANC [African National 
Congress]. Our political staff reports that it is now almost 
certain that the group will not participate in the election. 
[passage omitted] 
  The government's chief negotiator, Mr. Roelf Meyer, said the 
Alliance was making a big mistake in withdrawing from the 
negotiations. He said progress had been made in the past two 
weeks with the ANC and the government having made concessions. 
He said parties which did not take part in the election were 
minimizing their political roles. Mr. Meyer invited individual 
parties in the Alliance to take part in more negotiations. 

</TEXT>

