<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   AVF, DP Voice Misgivings Over Peacekeeping Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802135094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The leader of the Afrikaner Volksfront [National 
Front -- AVF], General Constand Viljoen, has called on political 
leaders to end the national peace force project as it will not 
serve its purpose. Speaking in Pretoria, Gen. Viljoen called on 
political leaders not to waste manpower on an experiment which 
the current commander acknowledged would not work. He said it 
bordered on the irresponsible to rush the force through training 
before turning it loose in a politically unstable country. 
  The DP [Democratic Party] candidate for the premiership in 
the Western Cape, Mr. Henie Bester, has said the National 
Peacekeeping Force is fast turning into a security farce. 
Speaking at an interparty breakfast meeting in Cape Town, he 
said alternative arrangements would have to be made urgently to 
ensure a free and fair election in April and economic growth 
afterwards. 

</TEXT>

