<H3> <TI>   TEC Admits to Some Problems in Peacekeeping Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802193494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Transitional Executive Council [TEC] has 
acknowledged that certain teething problems are being 
experienced with the National Peacekeeping Force. Following 
media criticism of the force, the TEC Subcouncil on Defense said 
it had held a meeting today with the commander of the force, 
Major General Gabriel Ramushwana, and the acting commander, 
Colonel Fred Burger. 
  The subcouncil and the force's command council would visit 
the training base at De Brug near Bloemfontein, and everything 
was being done to ensure that the peacekeeping force was a 
success. The subcouncil said a media day would be held at the 
base on Thursday [10 February]. 

</TEXT>

