<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   KwaZulu Police Commissioner Gives Evidence Before TEC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802191294 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1600 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Transitional Executive Council [TEC] today 
showed for the first time since its establishment that it is 
able to exercise its authority, when the chief of the kwaZulu 
Police [KZP], Lieutenant General Roy During, testified before 
the council after a long delay. This follows an earlier report 
by Justice Richard Goldstone on so-called hit squads in the KZP. 
This report by Ronel Van Zyl: 
  KZP Commissioner Lt. Gen. Roy During had up till today 
refused to respond to requests by the TEC that he appear before 
them. On Friday it was agreed that he would do so, after an 
out-of-court agreement between the TEC and the kwaZulu minister 
of police. Three KZP members were suspended after the Goldstone 
report. 
  In his evidence, Gen. During maintained that he was not 
aware 
of any other KZP members who were involved in hit squads. He 
added, however, that other allegations were being investigated 
by the South African Police at his request. Gen. During was 
pressed by questions on KZP members who had been trained by the 
South African Defense Force in Caprivi. It was obvious that the 
council wanted to determine whether there is any link between 
those KZP members trained in Caprivi and the hit squads. 
  Gen. During admitted that the allegations about hit squads 
in 
the KZP had been surfacing for many years. He emphasized that 
he had personally initiated investigations into these 
allegations, with the approval of Chief Minister Mangosuthu 
Buthelezi. At the end of the hearing the TEC did not make any 
ruling, except that the investigations into the matter were far 
from completed. Gen. During said he was prepared to appear 
again before the council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

