<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TEC Moves To Take Control of Broadcasting Licenses </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0802192694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0802192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Transitional Executive Council [TEC] has moved 
to take over control of broadcasting licenses from the 
government, and wants the Independent Broadcasting Authority to 
be in operation by the middle of next month. 
  A member of the TEC Management Committee, Mr. Mac Maharaj, 
said there was concern about the way in which Home Affair 
Minister Danie Schutte had granted temporary licenses to 15 
radio stations. He proposed that the TEC authorize the 
management committee to create a substructure to advise it on a 
process of short-listing applicants to the Independent 
Broadcasting Authority. 

</TEXT>

