<F P=102>  AB0902085194 Dakar PANA in English 1534 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0902085194 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lagos, 8 Feb. (NAN/PANA)--The minister of petroleum 
and mineral resources, Don Etiebet, left Lagos on Tuesday [8 
February] for a one-week visit to Saudi Arabia and Qatar to seek 
ways of increasing world crude oil prices. Etiebet will meet 
his Saudi counterpart, Hisham Muhyi-al-Din Nazir, and OPEC 
President 'Abdallah Bin-Hamad al-'Attiyah, who is also the 
minister of energy and industry in Qatar. Nigeria, Saudi Arabia 
and Qatar are members of OPEC. Etiebet said the trip had become 
necessary in view of the "ridiculous prices" of crude oil and 
called for measures to shore up the prices. 

