Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yaounde, Feb 9 (AFP) -- Cameroon president Paul Biya 
said at the time of the mini-summit meeting in Yamoussoukro that 
Cameroon would not leave the franc zone, the daily newspaper 
CAMEROON TRIBUNE reported on Wednesday [9 February]. 
  The newspaper said that the remarks by the president put an 
end to rumors appearing in parts of the French press that 
Cameroon would leave the franc zone in the wake of the 
devaluation of the CFA franc in mid-January. 
  The leader of the radical opposition, John Fru Ndi, 
suggested 
that Cameroon should exit the zone and create its own currency. 

