<F P=102>  EA1102150694 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1102150694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] After failing in its harmful activities in 
Somalia, the UN Operation Somalia II [UNOSOM] wants to illegally 
collect taxes at the country's ports and airports to the 
detriment of the objective of the struggling people, Abdi Hasan 
Awaleh Abdi Qaydid, chairman of the Somali National Alliance 
[SNA] high committee for internal affairs, said in an address to 
a rally at the 1 July Independence Square in Mogadishu. 
[passage omitted] 
  First, the rally was addressed by Abdulkadir Haji Mohamed, 
alias Luga-Dhere, member of the United Somali Congress [USC] 
Central Committee, who conveyed greetings to the people from 
Mohamed Farah Aidid, SNA and United Somali Congress chairman. 
He briefed the rally on new developments that occurred during 
the chairman's visits to some countries abroad. Luga-Dhere also 
said that UNOSOM has failed to trade on the Somali name to 
achieve its objectives. In conclusion, he said the world had 
been told clearly that UNOSOM would be held responsible for any 
problem that it might bring to the Somali people. 
  Abdi Hasan Awale Abdi Qaydid said Admiral Jonathan Howe must 
shoulder the responsibility for his problems. He said the 
Somali people will never forget the destruction Howe has brought 
upon them. He appealed to the world to bring him to justice. 
Abdi Qaydid also spoke of the illegal export of wild animals 
through the country's ports and airports. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

