<F P=101> Congo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Hires Israeli Mercenaries as Advisers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1002143694 Brussels LA LIBRE BELGIQUE in French 10 Feb 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BR1002143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels LA LIBRE BELGIQUE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by M.F.C.: "Israeli Mercenaries Are in Brazza; They </F>
Are Reported To Have Traveled via Belgium"] 
  [Text] The implementation of the contract signed by the 
Israelis and the Congolese Government has already started. 
According to information received by LA LIBRE BELGIQUE, on 26 
January about 10 Israelis reportedly traveled by Sabena to 
Kinshasa, which is separated from Brazzaville by no more than 
the Zaire River. We have not received confirmation of this 
information, but an investigation by the criminal investigation 
department is currently under way. 
<H5>  Already Paid </H5>
  In its issue of 3 February, the Paris-based LA LETTRE DU 
CONTINENT reported that "following an assessment mission, 15 
Israeli instructors have just set up in Brazzaville for 16 
months, in exchange for a payment of US$49 million. The first 
instalment at least has already been paid into a Swiss bank 
account." According to LA LETTRE DU CONTINENT, it was the 
Israeli ambassador in Kinshasa, Shlomo Avital, who had "taken 
care" of finalizing this "assistance agreement," although the 
contract is officially a private one. 
  LA LETTRE DU CONTINENT also indicates that "two Israeli 
advisers have joined the presidential staff in an individual 
capacity. One of them is a financial adviser and a member of 
the delegation currently visiting the IMF and the World Bank in 
Washington. The other is a traditional habitat adviser.... 
They have joined the president's new security adviser...." 

</TEXT>

