<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ghanaian Army Team Arrives for Peacekeeping Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1002200494 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise in French 0430 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1002200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While waiting for the establishment of the 
broad-based transitional institutions, the UN Assistance Mission 
in Rwanda [UNAMIR] has been reinforced by the arrival of new 
blue helmets. A contingent of 225 Ghanaian troops, part of the 
800-strong Ghanaian battalion, landed in Kigali yesterday. Its 
main task is to maintain security in the whole demilitarized 
area. 
  The other groups making up the Ghanaian battalion are 
expected before the end of the month. The commander of the 
Ghanaian contingent, Brigadier General Andoh, who has been in 
Rwanda for the past month, is also the second in command of the 
UNAMIR headquarters. With the arrival of new observers over the 
next few days, the number of UN mission troops will increase to 
2,600 troops and observers. 

</TEXT>

