<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   De Klerk, King Zwelithin Hold Talks in Durban </TI></H3>
<H4>   Crowd Boos de Klerk </H4>
<F P=102> MB1402192894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1704 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1402192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Durban Feb 14 SAPA -- Thousands of Zulus booed State 
President F W de Klerk when he emerged from Durban City Hall 
after a three-hour meeting with King Goodwill Zwelithini on 
Monday. The crowd also booed the joint statement tabled during 
the meeting when it was read to them and one man, tears 
streaming down his face, wailed aloud. 
  King Zwelithini, who was met with thunderous applause, 
calmed 
the crowd, telling them their patience would be rewarded. He 
called on his subjects to exercise restraint on their way home. 
The large crowd was expected to return to King's Park Stadium, 
from where they would be bused home. Before leaving, the crowd 
sang a farewell Zulu song to their monarch. 
  Police maintained a strong presence throughout and 
channelled 
people to their destinations. Durban's litter-strewn West 
Street emptied within minutes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

