<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Say ANC Making Political Issue of Office Raid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1102085094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1102085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The police have accused the ANC [African National 
Congress] of making a political issue of the raid on the ANC's 
office at Woodstock in Cape Town. 
  A police spokesman, General Leon Mellett, said it was a pity 
that the ANC had tried to politicize an incident in which the 
police were pursuing a criminal suspect. He said the suspect 
was being sought in connection with three murders, eight 
attempted murders, and the possession of explosives and unlawful 
firearms. The raid was carried out in response to information 
that the man had been involved in a shooting with three 
policemen in Khayelitsha. General Mellett said the ANC should 
say why it had hindered the police in their search of the 
building. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-25301 </DOCNO>
