<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Calls on UN To Stop Funding ANC, PAC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1202073694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1202073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has called on the United Nations to 
stop funding the ANC [African National Congress] and PAC 
[Pan-Africanist Congress]. In a letter to UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali, Foreign Affairs Minister Pik Botha drew his 
attention to a UN resolution in terms of which funds were to be 
given to the two organizations until their positions in South 
Africa had been normalized. Mr. Botha said that in the light of 
political developments in the country, and the organizations' 
registration as political parties, the requirements of the 
resolution had been met. 

</TEXT>

