<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   CP's Hartzenberg Dismisses NP's Call for Votes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1402115594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1136 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1402115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria Feb 14 SAPA -- Conservative Party leader 
Ferdi Hartzenberg on Monday [14 February] dismissed the National 
Party's [NP] call on Freedom Alliance supporters to vote for the 
NP in the elections as "laughable in the highest degree". 
  A vote for the NP was in fact a vote for the African 
National 
Congress [ANC], Dr Hartzenberg said in a statement. 
  The NP, in alliance with the African National Congress, had 
through secret deals and memoranda of understanding concocted a 
"draconian" constitution. "They who first let loose the 
communist monster and later notoriously capitulated before it, 
who could not control the ANC while they had all the government 
instruments at their disposal, now ask our people to support 
them as they enter the opposition benches." 
  This reminded one of the tale of the child who had murdered 
its parents and pleaded with the court for extenuating 
circumstances because he was now an orphan, Dr Hartzenberg said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

