<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Force Commander Quits `Controversial' Posts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1002154594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1002154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The commander of the National Peacekeeping Force, 
Major General Gabriel Ramushwana, says he has resigned from all 
his controversial posts. He said at the General De Wet Training 
Grounds in Bloemfontein that he had not only resigned as chief 
minister of Venda, but also from the Transitional Executive 
Council's subcouncil on defense. He was also no longer an ANC 
[African National Congress] candidate for the coming election. 
On the alleged poor hygiene at the base, Gen. Ramushwana said 
the situation had been caused by Transkei sending too many 
soldiers. Many of them had been sent back. 

</TEXT>

