<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Asked To Resign from Venda Defense Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1102162494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1102162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government is demanding the resignation of the 
commander of the National Peacekeeping Force, General Gabriel 
Ramushwana, as head of the Venda Defense Force. The minister of 
regional and land affairs, Mr. Andre Fourie, said in a statement 
in Pietersburg that General Ramushwana was still actively 
involved in political activities in Venda despite his position 
in the peace force. Mr. Fourie rejected accusations that he was 
undermining the peacekeepng force, saying that he was trying to 
protect the impartiality of the force. 

</TEXT>

