<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   APLA Commander Sabelo Phama Killed in Car Accident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1002135494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1002135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The commander of APLA [Azanian People's Liberation 
Army], Mr. Sabelo Phama, has been killed in a road accident in 
Tanzania. PAC [Pan-Africanist Congress] officials said in 
Johannesburg that the vehicle in which Mr. Phama was traveling 
with a bodyguard had been involved in a collision with a lorry 
while on his way to the Zimbabwean capital, Harare, from 
Tanzania. The bodyguard is in a critical condition in a 
hospital in Tanzania. 
  The officials said Mr. Phama had been on his way to Harare 
apparently to prepare for his return to South Africa where he 
was to assume a major role in the PAC's election campaign. He 
is expected to be buried in Transkei. 

</TEXT>

