<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Force Considering Strengthening Border Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1002073494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1002073494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Force is considering tougher steps to 
halt the deteriorating situation along the South African border 
with Mozambique and Swaziland. 
  Major General Reg Otto of Eastern Transvaal Command said the 
activities of armed smugglers, stock thieves, and people who 
cross the border illegally might compel the Defense Force to 
switch the electrified border fence from alarm to deadly 
strength. Gen. Otto said the security situation was becoming a 
burden on local infrastructure and agriculture. 

</TEXT>

