<H3> <TI>   ANC Delegation Arrives in Luanda on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1502074494 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1502074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An African National Congress [ANC] delegation 
arrived in Luanda today on an official visit at the invitation 
of the MPLA [Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola]. 
The delegation is headed by Tokyo Sexwale, a member of the ANC 
Executive Committee. Sexwale was welcomed by MPLA Secretary 
General Lopo do Nascimento. Speaking to journalists, Sexwale 
said he was particularly optimistic about the future of the 
South African people. 
  [Begin Sexwale recording, in English fading into Portuguese 
translation] We believe a democratic South Africa will play an 
important role in the region and will go a long way in helping 
the people of Angola themselves to solve their problems. [end 
recording] 
  This afternoon, the ANC delegation called at the MPLA 
headquarters to learn about the activities carried out by the 
party that won the first multiparty elections in Angola. Lopo 
do Nascimento discussed the activities of his party, leading to 
the September 1992 victory at the polls. He blamed the National 
Union for the Total Independence of Angola for the deplorable 
state of the country. 
  One of the main goals of the ANC delegation's visit to 
Angola 
is to learn about the Angolan elections because the first 
multiracial elections will be held in South Africa soon. Also 
today, the ANC delegation went to the Congressional Palace, 
where MPLA members of parliament told them about electoral 
systems. Tomorrow, the ANC delegation is scheduled to visit 
Benguela Province. 

</TEXT>

