<H3> <TI>   UN Commander Calls Renamo Officer's Remarks Absurd </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1102100794 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1102100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brazilian General Lelio Goncalves da Silva, 
commander of the UN peacekeeping force in Mozambique, has 
described as absurd, unfounded, and unjust the remarks made by 
Lieutenant General Mateus Ngonhamo, of the Mozambique National 
Resistance [Renamo]. Ngonhamo has said that the United Nations 
will be to blame, if war resumes in this country. 
  Gen. Lelio da Silva told NOTICIAS that the United Nations 
was 
invited by the government and Renamo to supervise the 
implementation of the Mozambican peace process, so Gen. 
Ngonhamo's remarks make no sense whatever. On 7 February, Gen. 
Ngonhamo said that a resumption of the war would have to be 
blamed on the United Nations, and in particular on UN Special 
Representative Aldo Ajello, who has not known how to be 
impartial when he has mediated in a bid to settle certain 
differences. 

</TEXT>

