<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unomoz Says Number of Confined Soldiers 36,574 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1402192994 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1402192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Over the weekend the government sent 1,491 soldiers 
to assembly areas opened by the United Nations. According to 
the daily UN Operations in Mozambique [Unomoz] report, in the 
same period the Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] sent 185 
soldiers to assembly areas. The government had by yesterday 
confined 23,543 soldiers, which represents 38 percent of the 
expected number of soldiers. Renamo had by yesterday confined 
10,021 soldiers, representing 52 percent of the expected number 
of soldiers. A total of 36,574 soldiers from both sides have 
already been confined. 

</TEXT>

