<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Personnel Training To Begin 21 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0902193294 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0902193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The first 5,000 government and Mozambique 
National Resistance [Renamo] troops joining the future 
Mozambican army, particularly its infantry division, begin their 
training in Dondo, Sofala Province, and in Manhica and Boane, 
Maputo Province, on 21 February. The government has already 
submitted the list of its 2,500 men to the British training 
team. Renamo still has to submit the list of its 2,500 men, but 
the organization says it will do so by 11 February. 
  This morning's session of the Joint Commission for the 
Formation of the Mozambique Defense Armed Forces discussed 
issues relating to the creation of the new Mozambican army -- 
namely, the type of organization, budget and logistics, and 
compliance with the dates set for the training of troops. The 
training of the 5,000 infantry soldiers will be given by 
instructors trained in Nyanga, Zimbabwe. British specialists 
will play an advisory role. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

