<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zimbabwe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ethiopian Envoy Formally Requests Mengistu Extradition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1502062294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1942 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1502062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Harare Feb 14 SAPA -- Ethiopian ambassador to 
Zimbabwe, Fantahun Michael, on Monday [14 February] confirmed 
his government is making a formal application to Zimbabwe to 
extradite former President Mengistu Haile Mariam. He told the 
ZIANA news agency: "I know it's in the process. But I don't 
know if the application has been formally lodged with the 
Zimbabwe Government." Zimbabwe Foreign Affairs Minister Nathan 
Shamuyarira could not be reached for comment. 
  Mr Michael told a press conference last week his government 
had been angered by recent statements by Mr Mengistu in which he 
defended his rule in Ethiopia and blamed unnamed members of his 
ruling circle for his overthrow, claiming they had been paid by 
"imperialist circles". The Zimbabwe Government also expressed 
displeasure at the statements. 
  Mr Mengistu was granted political asylum in Zimbabwe with 
his 
wife and children about 30 months ago on condition he did not 
engage in any political or public activity. 

</TEXT>

