<H3> <TI>   De Klerk, King Zwelithin Hold Talks in Durban </TI></H3>
<H4>   Shots Fired Outside City Hall </H4>
<F P=102> MB1402151894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1500 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1402151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] One person has been wounded in a shooting incident 
outside the City Hall in Durban. Several shots were fired into 
the air by people in the crowd of Zulu supporters gathered 
outside to wait for the outcome of talks between King Goodwill 
Zwelithini and State President F.W. de Klerk. The Zulu King was 
rushed outside along with Chief Minister Mangosuthu Buthelezi to 
placate the crowd. They told the gathering to stop shooting, and 
calm has now been restored. 

</TEXT>

