<H3> <TI>   De Klerk: Negotiated Settlement With Zulu King Possible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1502200494 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 1800 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1502200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President De Klerk says a negotiated settlement with 
King Goodwill and the far-right is still possible before the 
election date. He was speaking at a news conference at the 
Union Buildings after meeting Swedish Foreign Minister 
Margaretha af Ugglas. 
  [Begin De Klerk recording] We think that the anxieties and 
concerns of the Zulu king and Zulu leaders can be accommodated 
and our proposals will be aimed at formulating such 
accommodation. It will require from their side the will to find 
a compromise and it will require from their side also 
preparedness to move on very fixed stands on certain issues 
which have been taken, but I think there's a way out and we are 
not giving up until the very last moment. [end recording] 

