<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mandela Comments on Reports of SADF Disloyalty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1502105194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0955 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1502105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Feb 15 SAPA -- African National 
Congress [ANC] President Nelson Mandela says he is not concerned 
about reported disloyalty among certain elements within the 
South African Defence Force [SADF], SABC [South African 
Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reports. 
  Speaking at a news conference on Tuesday after meeting 
Swedish Foreign Minister Margaretha af Ugglas, Mr Mandela said 
he was convinced the democratic process had the full support of 
the majority of SADF members. 
  He was not worried about certain elements who wanted to 
cling 
to outdated policies as they would not affect the support the 
SADF was already giving to the negotiation process. 

</TEXT>

