<HT>    "drafr032_c_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-032 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TEC Says Composition of Peacekeeping Force Unacceptable </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1502202594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1902 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1502202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria Feb 15 SAPA -- The mostly black racial 
composition of the National Peacekeeping Force was unacceptable, 
the defence sub council of the Transitional Executive Council 
[TEC] has found. According to a summary of the sub-council's 
deliberations presented to the Executive Council on Tuesday, the 
Executive Management Committee has mandated a sub-committee to 
examine the problem. 
  The sub-council said the South African Defence Force had 
explained that without conscription there were no riflemen to 
draw upon and that new defence force recruits had not completed 
their training. 
  The sub council said practical solutions had to be found to 
rectify the racial composition if the peacekeeping force was to 
play a positive role in ensuring peaceful transition. 
  A joint Executive Council, defence force and defence sub 
council team is expected to finalise the peacekeeping force's 
budget by next week. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

