<H3> <TI>   Italian Defense Minister Says Hostages Released </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502125994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1137 GMT 
15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The two Italians held hostage in Somalia since last 
Saturday [12 February] were released this morning. The 
information was released by Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri. 
  The two men, Gianfranco Stefani and Sergio Passadore, are 
currently on their way to Mogadishu by helicopter. 
  It is yet known whether the $50,000 ransom demanded by the 
kidnappers was paid. 

</TEXT>

