<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Chief Denies Involvement in Sudanese Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1602230294 Kinshasa Voix du Zaire in French 1800 GMT 16 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1602230294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kinshasa Voix du Zaire </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here is a statement by the chief of general staff 
of the Zairian Armed Forces rejecting a statement by the 
Sudanese People's Liberation Army [SPLA] on Zaire's involvement 
in the Sudanese conflict. In a document that has just been 
handed to the news desk of La Voix du Zaire, General Eluki Monga 
Awundu says that Zairian territory does not serve and will not 
serve as a base for the incursion of foreign troops to settle an 
internal problem that does not concern Zaire. The problems 
between the SPLA and the Sudanese Armed Forces are purely 
internal to the Sudanese people, the document added. It 
concluded: The Zairian Armed Forces do not intend to support 
either of the two forces and urge the Sudanese to settle their 
problems like brothers. 

</TEXT>

