<H3> <TI>   UNITA Reportedly Fires on World Food Program Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1602201294 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1602201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA] today fired more than 20 machine gun rounds at an 
aircraft of the World Food Program and hit one of its wings. 
After carring out a mission in the province, the Boeing 727 
aircraft was shot at as it was returning to Luanda, where it 
made an emergency landing. We learned on the site that it will 
take some time before repair work can be carried out. UNITA is 
intensely shelling the city of Malange. 

