<H3> <TI>   South African Trade Mission Upgraded to Full Embassy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1602122694 Mbabane Radio Swaziland Network in English 1600 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1602122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mbabane Radio Swaziland Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The South African Trade Mission in Swaziland this 
week on Thursday [17 February] ceases to be a trade mission and 
becomes a fully fledged embassy. This, therefore, means that 
the South African trade representative, Mr. Heath, becomes the 
first South African ambassador to Swaziland, and Mr. Sam Malinga 
becomes Swaziland's first ambassador to South Africa after 
presentation of letters of credence by both ambassadors. 
Formalities to this effect will be finalized on Thursday when 
the South African trade representative meets the minister of 
foreign affairs, Mr. Solomon Dlamini. 
  Also to call on the foreign affairs minister on Thursday 
will 
be the United States ambassador designate to Swaziland, Dr. John 
Sprott. 

</TEXT>

