<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has denied reports that there is a 
rift and lack of confidence between the President and Minister 
Without Portfolio Brigadier General Godfrey Miyanda. A 
statement released to ZNBC [Zambia National Broadcasting 
Corporation] today by the government says the WEEKLY POST 
illegally obtained and published a memorandum from the president 
to Foreign Affairs Minister Dr. Remmy Mushota without 
authorization. The memo was published with intent to mislead 
the nation. 
  According to the statement, the first part of the memo was 
the president's comment on General Miyanda's performance in a 
television program. The second part was referring to an unnamed 
individual in the media who was making it difficult for the 
government to disseminate information. 

