<H3> <TI>   Mexico Decides To Relocate Embassy to South Africa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1602121894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1007 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1602121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Harare Feb 16 SAPA -- A decision by Mexico to 
relocate its mission to South Africa has left Zimbabwe "very 
unhappy", says Zimbabwean Foreign Affairs Minister Nathan 
Shamuyarira. According to the Mexicans the decision was taken 
for economic reasons, reports ZIANA news agency. Last month a 
senior Mexican diplomat was quoted as saying the mission in 
Zimbabwe had been experiencing financial problems. Mr 
Shamuyarira said his government was also disappointed at the 
level of trade between Mexico and Zimbabwe, which he described 
as "very low". 

</TEXT>

