<H3> <TI>   ECOMOG, UN Work Out Blueprint for Disarmament </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1602214094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 
16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1602214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A blue print for the disarmament and encampment of 
warring factions in Liberia is being worked out by ECOMOG 
[Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring 
Group] and the United Nations. The ECOMOG field commander, 
Major General John Inienger, made this known in Monrovia when 
the ambassadors of Egypt, Guinea, and Sierra Leone, paid him a 
courtesy visit. Maj. Gen. Inienger said that a disarmament 
committee had been set up to achieve the objectives of the peace 
process. He appealed to Egypt, Guinea, and Sierra Leone to 
assist [words indistinct] so that the disarmament would commence 
with the necessary logistic support. 

