<F P=101> Togo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Court Releases First-Round Election Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1602133894 Lome Radio Lome in French 1230 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1602133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The results of the first round of the legislative 
elections, which were held on 6 February, were announced by the 
Togolese Supreme Court this morning. During an ordinary session 
held at the courtroom of the Lome Court of Justice, the Supreme 
Court confirmed the results released by the National Electoral 
Commission [CEN] to the public. It agreed that the poll was 
held in a peaceful, safe, and honest atmosphere. The Supreme 
Court also agreed that 57 of the 352 contesting candidates 
obtained an absolute majority of votes and proclaimed them 
elected. It however observed that 48 other candidates, who did 
not obtain enough votes during the first round of the election, 
must contest the second round. The decree issued today approved 
all the results released by the CEN. The Supreme Court, which 
rejected petitions for cancellations, established that the 
turnout rate was about 65 to 70 percent and estimated that 
invalid votes were 37,407. 

</TEXT>

