<H3> <TI>   PAC's De Lille Says White Exodus `a Good Thing' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1602105094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
0430 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1602105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pan-Africanist Congress, PAC, Central Committee 
member Patricia de Lille says the white exodus from South Africa 
would be a good thing. Addressing a meeting of the 
International Press Institute in Cape Town, Ms. de Lille said 
the media had blown out of all proportion the white brain drain 
as if the whole country would come to a standstill as a result. 
Her statement is in contrast to African National Congress 
leader Mr. Nelson Mandela's call to whites not to leave the 
country. 

</TEXT>

